Name: HK_N_REP_DEF
Desc: Number of Report Definitions in the Report Definition List (maximum number of housekeeping/diagnostic reports)

Name: HK_MAX_SID
Desc: Maximum value of a service 3 Structure Identifier (SID)

Name: HK_MAX_N_ITEMS
Desc: Maximum number of data items in a housekeeping/diagnostic report

Name: HK_COLLECT_PER
Desc: Minimum collection period for service 3 reports

Name: HK_MAX_N_SIMPLE
Desc: Maximum number of simply-commutated parameters in a housekeeping or diagnostic report

Name: HK_MAX_N_GR
Desc: Maximum number of super-commutated groups in a housekeeping/diagnostic report

Name: HK_MAX_REP
Desc: Maximum value of the repetition number of a super-commutated group in a housekeeping/diagnostic report

Name: HK_MAX_N_REP
Desc: Maximum number of data items in a super-commutated groups in a housekeeping/diagnostic report

Name: HK_MAX_ID
Desc: Maximum value of a data pool item identifier

Name: HK_N_SAMP_BUF
Desc: Number of service 3 Sampling Buffers

Name: HK_N_DEBUG_VAR
Desc: Number of debug variables

Name: EVT_N_ID
Desc: Number of event identifiers supported by the application

Name: TST_N_DEST
Desc: Number of destinations managed by test service

Name: LPT_N_BUF
Desc: Number of Large Packet Transfer Buffers available for down-or up-transfer of large packets

Name: MON_N_PMON
Desc: Maximum number of entries in the Parameter Monitoring Definition List PMDL (maximum number of parameter monitors in the application)

Name: MON_N_LIM
Desc: Maximum number of parameter monitors with a limit check

Name: MON_N_EXP
Desc: Maximum number of parameter monitors with an expected value check

Name: MON_N_DEL
Desc: Maximum number of parameter monitors with a delta value check

Name: MON_PER
Desc: Minimum monitoring period

Name: MON_N_CLST
Desc: Maximum number of entries in the Check Transition List

Name: MON_N_FMON
Desc: Maximum number of entries in the Functional Monitoring Definition List FMDL (maximum number of functional monitors in the application)

Name: MON_N_PFMON
Desc: Maximum number of parameter monitors in a functional monitor

Name: MON_NFPMON
Desc: Maximum number of functional monitors to which the same parameter monitor may belong

Name: MON_FPER
Desc: Period of execution of the Functional Monitoring Procedure expressed as a multiple of MON_PER

Name: SCD_N_TBA
Desc: Number of time-based scheduled activities

Name: SCD_N_SUB_TBS
Desc: Number of time-based sub-schedules

Name: SCD_N_GROUP
Desc: Number of time-based schedule groups
